                            <comment id="12731246" author="rafan" created="Wed, 15 Jul 2009 02:44:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This doc changes look good except we may want to use example.com instead of foo.com for illustration. In addition, we may want to mention which ZooKeeper version is recommended if users want to use their own ZK Quorum. Also, a memory requirement for ZK would be nice (like you said on mailing, at least 1GB).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12731273" author="stack" created="Wed, 15 Jul 2009 05:13:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;.bq See &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;$&lt;/p&gt;
{HBASE_HOME}
&lt;p&gt;/conf/hbase-default.xml&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; for more information about the available ZooKeeper properties.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The above sentence is a little misleading in that it points to hbase-default.xml as authority on what properties you can set in hbase-site.xml.  Rather, isn&apos;t zoo.cfg the authority and hbase-default.xml has a subset?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Otherwise, doc. is excellent.  +1 on committing after addressing Rong-en&apos;s concerns to.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12731578" author="nitay" created="Wed, 15 Jul 2009 17:36:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review Rong-En / Stack. Here&apos;s the second patch with fixes to everything you guys mentioned.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
